extends layout

block content
	#page
		#cbox1
			h2 Hardware Modules

			div(class="row-fluid", style="padding-top:20px; margin-left:50px")
				h3 1. Microcontroller & Accessories
				
				div(class="row-fluid")
					h4(class="span2", style="padding-top:10px") 
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/11021", target="_blank") Arduino Uno ($30)
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/11021", style="padding:10px", class="link-style", target="_blank") Buy Now
					img(src="images/uno.jpg", height="200", class="span2")
					div(class="span3", style="padding-top:20px") The Arduino Uno is our microcontroller of choice. The Arduino platform has a thriving community which is great when looking for libraries to interact with new hardware. Itâ€™s programmed in C/C++.
			

					h3(class="span3 offset1", style="padding-top:10px") Hardware You'll Need
					div(class="span3 offset1")
						ol
							li Buy recommended Arduino and header pins. 
							li Buy recommended WiFly module for internet connectivity.
							li If you plan to use RFID, purchase recommended RFID reader and fobs. 

				div(class="row-fluid")
					h4(class="span2", style="padding-top:10px")
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10007", target="_blank") Stackable Header Kit for Arduino ($1.50)
						br
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10007", style="padding:10px", class="link-style", target="_blank") Buy Now
					img(src="images/headerPins.jpg", height="200", class="span2")
					div(class="span3", style="padding-top:20px") You'll need this header pin kit for stacking the Arduino shields. We'd recommend buying two of these. 


			div(class="row-fluid", style="margin-left:50px")
				h3 2. Internet connectivity
				
				div(class="row-fluid", style="padding-top:10px")
					h4(class="span2", style="padding-top:10px") 
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10822", target="_blank") WiFly Module ($30)
						a(href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/10822", style="padding:10px", class="link-style", target="_blank") Buy Now
					img(src="images/wifly.jpg", height="200", class="span2")
					div(class="span3", style="padding-top:20px") We have found the Sparkfun WiFly module to be the best form factor for internet connectivity. You just need to hook up the TX, RX, VCC, and GND pins to an Arduino to get it working. 				
				
	
			div(class="row-fluid", style="padding-top:10px; margin-left:50px") 
				h3 3. RFID
				
				div(class="row-fluid")
					h4(class="span2", style="padding-top:10px")
						a(href="http://www.adafruit.com/products/789", target="_blank") RFID Reader ($40)
						a(href="http://www.adafruit.com/products/789", style="padding:10px", class="link-style", target="_blank") Buy Now
					img(src="images/rfidreader.jpg", height="200", class="span2")
					div(class="span3", style="padding-top:20px") This is an Arduino shield designed for reading MiFare 13.56MHz RFIDs. Adafruit also has software libraries for this shield that work really well.

				div(class="row-fluid", style="padding-top:30px")
					h4(class="span2", style="padding-top:10px")
						a(href="http://www.adafruit.com/products/363", target="_blank") RFID Fob ($2.50)
						a(href="http://www.adafruit.com/products/363", style="padding:10px", class="link-style", target="_blank") Buy Now
					img(src="images/mifarefob.jpg", height="200", class="span2")
					div(class="span3", style="padding-top:20px") MiFare is a widely accepted RFID standard. These fobs come with 1k of storage so that you can have additional information about someone stored on their key tags.
	
